13:42.366 --> 13:44.577
No "ew. " It's natural, honey.

13:44.702 --> 13:46.079
Shameful and natural.

13:46.204 --> 13:47.547
Just get out!

13:47.672 --> 13:49.649
Good night, you Prince
of New England.

13:49.774 --> 13:52.552
You Tom's of Maine.

13:52.677 --> 13:54.721
You want a bedtime song?

13:54.846 --> 13:57.023
♪ I'm never gonna let you go ♪

13:57.148 --> 14:01.394
♪ I'm gonna hold you
in my arms forever ♪

14:01.519 --> 14:06.166
♪ Gonna try to make up
for the times I hurt you so... ♪

14:06.291 --> 14:08.168
Good-bye, room. Forever.

14:08.293 --> 14:10.103
♪ Gonna hold your body
close to mine ♪

14:10.228 --> 14:12.271
♪ From this day on,
we're gonna be together ♪

14:12.396 --> 14:13.773
I'll need these on the road.

14:13.898 --> 14:15.008
God willing, I'll have enough time

14:15.133 --> 14:16.275
to slide them on my attackers.

14:16.400 --> 14:17.773
♪ Oh, I swear this time ♪

14:17.939 --> 14:21.905
♪ I'm never gonna let you go. ♪

14:27.134 --> 14:27.844
Brian!

14:27.969 --> 14:29.046
I'll kill you, Debra!

14:29.171 --> 14:30.347
Oh, Steve.

14:30.472 --> 14:31.815
Oh, thank God.

14:31.940 --> 14:32.983
Thought you were Debra.

14:33.108 --> 14:35.018
What are you doing out at this hour?

14:35.143 --> 14:36.920
My legal guardian was killing me.

14:37.045 --> 14:38.755
I can't be in that house anymore.

14:38.880 --> 14:40.457
It's all his fault you got evicted.

14:40.582 --> 14:41.925
Oh, I'm past that, Steve.

14:42.050 --> 14:44.127
I'm gonna hit the
road, get out of town,

14:44.252 --> 14:45.695
eat some of these oranges.

14:45.820 --> 14:47.030
It totally sucks here!

14:47.155 --> 14:48.498
Let me come with you.

14:48.623 --> 14:49.805
Yeah, sure.

14:49.971 --> 14:52.093
Get down!

14:54.559 --> 14:57.007
Lew-Lew!

14:57.132 --> 14:59.042
I ain't mad at you.

14:59.167 --> 15:02.769
I just want to talk to you.

15:12.881 --> 15:14.258
Oklahoma?!

15:14.383 --> 15:16.493
Wow! How long was I asleep?

15:16.618 --> 15:18.896
Steve, I'll be perfectly honest.

15:19.021 --> 15:20.998
I thought you were
awake this whole time.

15:21.123 --> 15:22.632
I told you my life story.

15:22.757 --> 15:24.401
Hell, I told you about my stepmom.

15:24.526 --> 15:26.236
Thought you were in a stunned silence

15:26.361 --> 15:28.462
that somebody could
do that to a child.

15:30.032 --> 15:31.975
Man, I can't wait till we get to...

15:32.100 --> 15:33.310
Wait- where are we going?

15:33.435 --> 15:34.934
The Grand Canyon.

15:35.100 --> 15:36.914
Ooh, I'll have freedom out there.

15:37.039 --> 15:38.515
No one making me eat healthy

15:38.640 --> 15:41.023
and tickling my back
even when I don't want it.

15:41.189 --> 15:42.352
That's not right.

15:42.477 --> 15:45.055
Now, a grown black man
and a young white boy

15:45.180 --> 15:47.881
driving cross country-
that feels right.

15:51.283 --> 15:53.797
Now that there- that is sick.

15:53.922 --> 15:55.799
Y'all got a lot of nerve!

15:55.924 --> 15:58.040
This is a public road!

16:00.751 --> 16:03.440
Officer, he's not in the house,
he's not answering his phone.

16:03.565 --> 16:04.774
I'm his guardian.

16:04.899 --> 16:06.609
If anything happens to him,
I'm responsible...

16:06.734 --> 16:07.883
Calm down?

16:08.049 --> 16:09.212
Calm down?!

16:09.337 --> 16:10.504
Okay.

16:16.016 --> 16:17.854
He was exactly right.

16:17.979 --> 16:20.563
That was good advice.

16:20.729 --> 16:21.891
So, I was thinking

16:22.016 --> 16:24.061
about how we could make
a living in Arizona.

16:24.186 --> 16:25.262
I will be a dancer.

16:25.387 --> 16:26.787
What are your skills, Brian?

16:28.923 --> 16:30.500
Oh, Steve.

16:30.625 --> 16:32.700
We're not going to
Arizona to live together.

16:32.866 --> 16:35.661
We're going there to die together.

16:35.827 --> 16:37.640
Uh... pardon me?

16:37.765 --> 16:39.742
I've got nothing left
to live for, Steve.

16:39.867 --> 16:43.169
Which is why I'm driving us
straight into thGrand Canyon.

16:44.169 --> 16:46.116
Suicide, bitch!

16:46.241 --> 16:47.941
Canyon style!

16:51.259 --> 16:52.622
Tickets! Tickets!

16:52.747 --> 16:53.679
Extra tickets.

16:53.845 --> 16:55.725
This place is totally screwing us.

16:55.850 --> 16:58.795
Yeah, well, they're not the only
ones who can do the screwing.

16:58.920 --> 17:00.063
I beg your pardon?

17:00.188 --> 17:01.898
Their stupid water park screws us,

17:02.023 --> 17:05.402
we do the same thing...
to each other.

17:05.527 --> 17:08.671
And we do it in there,
on the biggest slide they got.

17:08.796 --> 17:10.807
Of course that's what we do.

17:10.932 --> 17:13.143
That's brilliant!

17:13.268 --> 17:14.810
Dan?

17:14.935 --> 17:16.646
Dan!

17:16.771 --> 17:18.882
Don't tell my wife where I am.

17:19.007 --> 17:24.085
She's the biggest bitch
in the universe!

17:26.647 --> 17:27.957
Freddy, I can't find Steve.

17:28.082 --> 17:30.060
I haven't seen him
since you introduced us.

17:30.185 --> 17:31.628
This is all your fault, Frederick.

17:31.753 --> 17:33.096
You were his approved friend.

17:33.221 --> 17:35.798
You're supposed to watch out
for him when I'm not around.

17:35.923 --> 17:37.057
You're supposed to...

17:39.594 --> 17:41.018
Don't do that, man.

17:41.184 --> 17:43.240
Look, Steve left
because you smother him.

17:43.365 --> 17:46.376
I'm a good kid because
my parents allow me the freedom

17:46.501 --> 17:47.577
to be myself.

17:47.702 --> 17:49.979
Can you imagine
how nervous they must have been

17:50.104 --> 17:52.196
when I said
I was hanging out with you?

17:52.362 --> 17:55.366
I suppose I am a dangerous,
aggressive stranger.

17:55.532 --> 17:57.220
They let me make my own mistakes,

17:57.345 --> 18:00.121
but I know they're always there
when I need them.

18:00.287 --> 18:02.859
Damn it, Freddy, I've been a fool.

18:02.984 --> 18:04.961
It's not enough to love your kid.

18:05.086 --> 18:07.164
You have to love 'em the right way.

18:07.289 --> 18:08.998
I know what I have to do.

18:09.123 --> 18:11.234
I just hope I can find Steve in time.

18:11.359 --> 18:12.436
Well, I'm glad that...

18:12.561 --> 18:15.136
Be glad about that.

18:17.929 --> 18:18.975
Okay, here's the plan.

18:19.100 --> 18:20.477
You go down first and wait

18:20.602 --> 18:22.079
at the bottom in a ready position.

18:22.204 --> 18:24.347
I'm gonna come down after you,
and by the time

18:24.472 --> 18:26.550
I get to the bottom,
I'll be ready to go.

18:26.675 --> 18:28.642
I'll be there to receive you.

18:30.483 --> 18:32.446
♪ ♪

18:36.017 --> 18:37.908
I'm coming in too hot!
Move back!

18:38.074 --> 18:39.785
What?!

18:39.951 --> 18:40.887
Stan, slow down!

18:47.375 --> 18:50.340
Brian, I don't want
to die in the Grand Canyon.

18:50.465 --> 18:52.065
Please! I thought we were friends.

18:53.301 --> 18:54.444
You thought I let you

18:54.569 --> 18:56.413
in the teacher's lounge
because I like you?

18:56.538 --> 18:58.248
You were my accountant, Steve.

18:58.373 --> 19:00.183
Roger was right.

19:00.308 --> 19:02.892
Ah, and there she is.

19:11.650 --> 19:13.152
Roger!

19:13.318 --> 19:15.237
You! How did you find us?

19:15.403 --> 19:16.399
It was simple.

19:16.524 --> 19:18.168
When you love someone hard enough,

19:18.293 --> 19:20.117
you always know where they are.

19:20.283 --> 19:21.838
That can't possibly be true.

19:21.963 --> 19:23.440
Roger, thank God!

19:23.565 --> 19:24.741
I want to go home!

19:24.866 --> 19:26.143
I can't do that, Steve.

19:26.268 --> 19:28.111
You see this gun I'm pointing at you?

19:28.236 --> 19:30.113
That's what I've been doing
this whole week-

19:30.238 --> 19:31.615
holding you hostage.

19:31.740 --> 19:33.339
Well, not anymore.

19:33.505 --> 19:34.784
What?! No!

19:34.909 --> 19:37.426
Principal Lewis is gonna
drive off the Grand Canyon!

19:37.592 --> 19:39.088
You'll be fine, Steve.

19:39.213 --> 19:41.625
I came here to tell you,
you'll be fine.

19:41.750 --> 19:44.099
And I'll be supporting you
all the way.

19:44.265 --> 19:45.428
Shoot Principal Lewis now!

19:45.553 --> 19:47.597
I love you way too much for that.

19:47.722 --> 19:48.889
See ya, sucker!

19:50.855 --> 19:51.768
Good-bye, bad credit!

19:51.893 --> 19:54.735
Oh, my God!

19:58.199 --> 19:59.276
I don't believe it.

19:59.401 --> 20:01.909
Roger's love is keeping us aloft.

20:03.493 --> 20:04.829
We're gonna make it.

20:04.995 --> 20:06.816
So long, junk mail!

20:06.941 --> 20:08.207
Wait. What?

20:15.255 --> 20:16.793
Steve, I'm so sorry.

20:16.918 --> 20:18.761
I never meant for you to get hurt.

20:18.886 --> 20:20.497
I'm a terrible legal guardian.

20:20.622 --> 20:22.763
You are the worst legal guardian.

20:22.929 --> 20:24.434
I'm sorry, too, Steve.

20:24.559 --> 20:26.403
Surviving that crash made me reize,

20:26.528 --> 20:29.639
I'm on this earth for a reason-
to shape young minds.

20:29.764 --> 20:32.542
I'm gonna get my job back
as principal,

20:32.667 --> 20:35.276
and this time,
I'm gonna do everything right.

20:35.442 --> 20:37.214
Time for your bath, Mr. Lewis?

20:37.339 --> 20:38.715
Please.

20:38.840 --> 20:40.584
Mr. Lewis was my father.

20:40.709 --> 20:43.877
Call me Chocolate Dinosaur.

20:44.912 --> 20:46.620
Dad! Mom!

20:46.786 --> 20:48.658
Steve! Roger!

20:48.783 --> 20:50.159
What the hell is going on?

20:50.284 --> 20:51.728
Well, it looks like you tried

20:51.853 --> 20:53.330
to slingshot yourself into Francine.

20:53.455 --> 20:54.503
Didn't you, Stan?

20:54.669 --> 20:56.630
I came in too hot.

20:56.796 --> 20:58.535
This is the worst day of my life.

20:58.660 --> 21:00.551
Well, you're not getting
your morphine back.

21:00.717 --> 21:01.838
Roger, give it back!

21:01.963 --> 21:03.139
Don't be such a jerk!

21:03.264 --> 21:04.341
God, I'm sick of you!

21:04.466 --> 21:05.709
Come on! Give it! Freddy!

21:05.834 --> 21:07.568
Damn it, Roger, come on!

21:10.843 --> 21:12.716
Freddy.

